cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper focuses on unsupervised learning of transformation-equivariant representations for visual structures, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel principled method for training the networks, which involves maximizing mutual information and variational lower-bound, indicating a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) experiments, suggesting a possible connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
